All the system service code is under directory\frameworks\base\services\java\com\android\server, but I can't find where is the main entrance to run my Service.
Is there a general way to create a new system service and run?
Thank you in advance.
Update 1:  
I want to create a system service that need to store message in sqlite db.

A: Alas the System service are nothing but special service to handle all important thing for the System. The System is amount to run 3 main services, Core Service, Frameworks and nativeapp Services. Run the services is nothing but calling the function onCreate(). So you need to Find the base class of the Service you want to create....
Like you want to create the Service to store the message to the sqlite db. You need to find all the existing service for this Scenario and create new or extend the existing....
The Base class is nothing but the Service class.
To create your new System service:

*

*Create new java file

*Make sure you are extending the System service base class. (Depend on the case) public class YourService extends Service

*Implement the Implemtation for the service using the onCreate().....

